            <h1>Sandplay Therapy</h1>
            <h2>——how it works</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="paragraph">
            <p>
                Sandplay is a powerful therapeutic technique that facilitates the psyche’s natural capacity for healing.<br/>
                In a “free and protected” space provided by the analyst, a client creates a concrete manifestation of his or her imaginal world using sand, water, and miniature objects.<br/>
                In this way Sandplay helps honor and illuminate the client’s internal symbolic world and provides a place for its expression within a safe container, the tray filled with sand. With sufficient time and understanding, this experience can lead to the development of a new psychic structure of the personality.
            </p>
            <div class="quote">
                <h3>Terms</h3>
                <p>
                    Individualization<br/>
                    ——A person eventually becomes himself, which is integrated, indivisible and distinct from others<br/>
                    Archetype<br/>
                    ——The accumulation of primitive human experience. They are with us all the time just like fate, and are affecting our lives<br/>
                    Archetypal images<br/>
                    ——The form in which archetype presents itself to consciousness. We can understand the existence of the archetype and its meaning through the archetypal images
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <img src="/images/sandword/5.png" class="img-full-width">
        <div class="paragraph">
            <h3>Advantages</h3>
            <p>
                When the cause of psychological distress is complicated, subconscious can express itself instead of language.<br/>
                The game itself is a cure as a human nature.<br/>
                Interesting treatments can reduce the user's psychological confrontation.<br/>
                Sandplay therapy does not address a specific problem. It is universal and helpful for the average people.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
